    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nSetting `cterm` / `gui` attribute for highlight group in `nvim --clean` prevents corresponding `cterm{fg,bg}` / `gui{fg,bg}` attributes to be updated after changing background.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean`\r\n2. `:hi Comment cterm=underline`\r\n3. `:hi Comment` and remember values of all attributes. On current `master` it would be `cterm=underline ctermfg=247 guifg=NvimLightGrey4`. Prior to default color scheme update (at 481a3158866638946c91fab28ae5bca97ff1e814) it was `cterm=underline ctermfg=14 guifg=#80a0ff`.\r\n4. `:set bg=light` (assuming initial value was \"dark\").\r\n5. `:hi Comment` and see which values have changed. On current `master` it is observed to be `cterm=underline ctermfg=247 guifg=NvimDarkGrey4`. Prior to default color scheme update it is `cterm=underline ctermfg=14 guifg=Blue`. Both of them have `guifg` changed while `ctermfg` remains the same.\r\n\r\n------\r\n\r\nThis doesn't seem to be a new issue, because it is reproducible on at least 0.6.1.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nHaving highlight group partially manually updated should not restrict it to be updated according to the default color scheme. If reproduction steps are done without `:hi Comment cterm=underline`, this is the expected output:\r\n- On current `master`: `ctermfg=239 guifg=NvimDarkGrey4`.\r\n- On previous default color scheme: `ctermfg=4 guifg=Blue`.\r\n\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-1857+g7cae94e91\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64 (6.6.3-arch1-1)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst-0.9\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nBoth appimage and from source",
